  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nCurrently the only way to access `_operatorApprovals` in the [ERC721](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol) contract is via `setApprovalForAll()`, which is a public function that only sets operator approvals for the message sender.\r\n\r\nI think it would be beneficial to refactor this into an internal virtual function that takes an additional `owner` parameter. This would allow expanded functionality such as a `permitForAll()` function, setting an operator approval via a meta-transaction. This also brings the flow closer to how `approve()` is handled.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nAdd a function to the ERC721 contract:\r\n```\r\nfunction _setOperatorApproval(address owner, address operator, bool approved) internal virtual {\r\n    _operatorApprovals[owner][operator] = approved;\r\n    emit ApprovalForAll(owner, operator, approved); \r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRefactor the `setApprovalForAll()` function in the ERC721 contract:\r\n```\r\nfunction setApprovalForAll(address operator, bool approved) public virtual override {\r\n    require(operator != _msgSender(), \"ERC721: approve to caller\");\r\n\r\n    _setOperatorApproval(_msgSender(), operator, approved);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nI think that's all it takes, let me know what you think!\r\n",
